TY  - JOUR
T1  - Dynamic Programming Approach for Valuing Options in the GARCH Model
AU  - Ben-Ameur, Hatem
AU  - Breton, Michèle
AU  - Martinez, Juan-Manuel
Y1  - 2008/10/10
PY  - 2008
DA  - 2009/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.1080.0925
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.1080.0925
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 252
EP  - 266
VL  - 55
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In this paper, we develop an efficient algorithm to value options under discrete-time GARCH processes. We propose a procedure based on dynamic programming coupled with piecewise polynomial approximation to compute the value of a given option, at all observation dates and levels of the state vector. The method can be used for the large GARCH family of models based on Gaussian innovations and may accommodate all low-dimensional European as well as American derivatives. Numerical implementations show that this method competes very advantageously with other available valuation methods.
AB  - In this paper, we develop an efficient algorithm to value options under discrete-time GARCH processes. We propose a procedure based on dynamic programming coupled with piecewise polynomial approximation to compute the value of a given option, at all observation dates and levels of the state vector. The method can be used for the large GARCH family of models based on Gaussian innovations and may accommodate all low-dimensional European as well as American derivatives. Numerical implementations show that this method competes very advantageously with other available valuation methods.
