TY  - JOUR
T1  - Simulating Sensitivities of Conditional Value at Risk
AU  - Hong, L. Jeff
AU  - Liu, Guangwu
Y1  - 2008/09/05
PY  - 2008
DA  - 2009/02/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.1080.0901
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.1080.0901
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 281
EP  - 293
VL  - 55
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Conditional value at risk (CVaR) is both a coherent risk measure and a natural risk statistic. It is often used to measure the risk associated with large losses. In this paper, we study how to estimate the sensitivities of CVaR using Monte Carlo simulation. We first prove that the CVaR sensitivity can be written as a conditional expectation for general loss distributions. We then propose an estimator of the CVaR sensitivity and analyze its asymptotic properties. The numerical results show that the estimator works well. Furthermore, we demonstrate how to use the estimator to solve optimization problems with CVaR objective and/or constraints, and compare it to a popular linear programming-based algorithm.
AB  - Conditional value at risk (CVaR) is both a coherent risk measure and a natural risk statistic. It is often used to measure the risk associated with large losses. In this paper, we study how to estimate the sensitivities of CVaR using Monte Carlo simulation. We first prove that the CVaR sensitivity can be written as a conditional expectation for general loss distributions. We then propose an estimator of the CVaR sensitivity and analyze its asymptotic properties. The numerical results show that the estimator works well. Furthermore, we demonstrate how to use the estimator to solve optimization problems with CVaR objective and/or constraints, and compare it to a popular linear programming-based algorithm.
SN  - 0025-1909
M3  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.1080.0901
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.1080.0901
Y2  - 2024/03/28
